'''Massimo Vigliar''' (born February 9, 1949 in [[Rome]], [[Italy]]) is an Italian film [[Film producer|producer]].

== Career ==
In 1982 he founded Surf Film, which operates in the sector of worldwide productions and distributions with a which now counts approximately 600 films..<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.surffilm.com |title=Surf Film |publisher=Surf Film |date= |accessdate=2014-05-06}}</ref> Many of them represent part of the greatest productions of [[Post-war]] Italian Cinema, such as "[[Two Women]]”, "[[Marriage Italian Style]]”, "[[Yesterday, Today and Tomorrow]]” by [[Vittorio De Sica]]; "[[A Special Day]]” by [[Ettore Scola]], "[[Django (1966 film)|Django]]" by [[Sergio Corbucci]] amongst many others.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.surffilm.com |title=Surf Film |publisher=Surf Film |date= |accessdate=2014-05-06}}</ref> The list also contains unforgettable pieces of European Cinema such as ‘[[Contempt (film)|Contempt]]’ by [[Jean-Luc Godard|Jean Luc Godard]], and ‘[[Quiet Days in Clichy (1990 film)|Quiet Days in Clichy]]’ by [[Claude Chabrol|C. Chabrol]]. He produced "[[Gorbaciof]]" with [[Toni Servillo]], directed by [[:it:Stefano Incerti|Stefano Incerti]], which was shown at the [[67th Venice International Film Festival]], receiving widespread critical acclaim and competing at the [[2010 Toronto International Film Festival|35th Festival of Toronto]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Di Paolo D'Agostini |url=http://www.repubblica.it/spettacoli-e-cultura/2010/10/15/news/servillo_gorbaciov-8069984/?ref=search |title=Servillo-Gorbaciof tira dritto sulla strada delle emozioni forti |publisher=Repubblica.it |date=2013-04-29 |accessdate=2014-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Jay Weissberg |url=https://variety.com/2010/film/reviews/gorbaciof-1117943425/ |title=Gorbaciof |publisher=Variety |date=2010-09-03 |accessdate=2014-05-06}}</ref> Recently, Vigliar has devoted himself to the production of numerous documentaries remembering some of the fundamental contributors to the greatness of Italian cinema [[Cinema of Italy|Italian Cinema]] such as Vittorio De Sica and [[Sophia Loren]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.surffilm.com |title=Surf Film |publisher=Surf Film |date= |accessdate=2014-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.italica.rai.it/scheda.php?scheda=loren_premioacting_sophia_ierioggidomani |title=Sophia: ieri, oggi e domani – Conversazione con Sophia Loren – Extra |publisher=Italica |date= |accessdate=2014-05-06}}</ref> He also operates in cinema productions in the United Kingdom and Spain.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.empresia.es/persona/vigliar-massimo/ |title=VIGLIAR MASSIMO. Cargos directivos |language=es |publisher=Empresia.es |date= |accessdate=2014-05-06}}</ref>

== Personal life ==

Vigliar has been [[Philanthropy|philanthropically]] involved in [[Africa]]. In 2009 he funded the construction of a health centre in [[Thyolo]], [[Malawi]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Charles Sinetre |url=http://mzunguwatipaso.blogspot.co.uk/2010_09_09_archive.html |title=Maranatha Mzungu: Sep 9, 2010 |publisher=Mzunguwatipaso.blogspot.co.uk |date=2010-09-09 |accessdate=2014-05-06}}</ref>

